===Etymology===
From {{L.}} [[bryum]] "moss" + [[-ophyta]]

===Proper noun===
'''Bryophyta'''

#{{botany}}: A [[botanical name]] for a [[taxon]] within [[kingdom]] [[Plantae]] that includes the [[moss]]es. The taxon is traditionally given the [[rank]] of a [[division]].
#{{italbrac|botany, obsolete}}: A [[botanical name]] at the rank of [[division]] or [[phylum]] including all the [[bryophyte]]s (the [[moss]]es, [[liverwort]]s, and [[hornwort]]s).

